<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-31-1036 </DOCNO><TEXT>Public attitudes towards the accident at Chernobyl in April 1986 are discussed.Although affected by the radioactive fallout from Chernobyl, people inWest Germany were still prepared to vote, only 3 months later, for politicalparties who would not change the nuclear situation, not for the 'Greens'who would. The whole issue is seen as a question of values and alternatives.</TEXT></DOC>